features: MULTIFUNCTIONAL: Now you can air fry, bake, broil, convection bake, convection broil, toast, and warm, all in one great-looking, space-saving toaster oven air fryer combo
FAMILY SIZE: Thoughtfully designed to cook for a crowd, the spacious 20-quart capacity fits four slices of toast, a 10-inch pizza, or a whole 5.5lb chicken
VERSATILE TEMPS: Whether you’re toasting a bagel, air frying French fries, or baking cookies, the Toast-Air has you covered with a temperature range from 200-450˚F
HEALTHIER COOKING: Use 98% less oil when you air fry chicken or vegetables for healthy meals made simple

body.description: With the Chefman Toast-Air Convection Oven + Air Fryer, you can air fry, bake, broil, convection bake, toast, and warm all in one convenient countertop cooking appliance. With a temperature range from 200-450°F and seven cooking functions, making great meals has never been easier! The extra-large 20-quart lighted interior can fit up to 4 slices of toast, roast a 5.5lb chicken, and fits most baking pans. The integrated 60-minute countdown timer lets you know when your food is ready, and the unit automatically shuts off when opened for added safety. The dishwasher-safe air fry basket, cooking rack, broil pan, and removable crumb tray keep cleanup simple. 120 Volts/1800 Watts.7-in-1 air fryer oven.Preset cooking functions (air fry, bake, broil, convection bake, convection broil, toast, and warm). Temperature range from 200-450°F. Automatic shut-off. Cool-touch handle. Interior light for easy viewing. Nonstick dishwasher-safe parts. Baking rack, air fry basket, broil pan. Cookbook included.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks good, works okay, just fits in the space I measured.
reviews.reviewText: Looks good, seems to work okay so far.Those who say the toast function doesn't work, keep reading.I purchased this specifically to fit in my 15" wide x 14" tall appliance garage, It sticks out a bit too far to close the garage door, but I plan to use it daily. Hopefully the heat does not discolor the cabinets over time. It does not seem to get super hot on the exterior when in use, but I have not ran it more than 15 minutes at a time so far. Thankfully it doesn't have a super dorky weird-sounding brand name like so many Amazon products, since it is on display in my kitchen.I am happy that it seems to have all mechanical controls, meaning no circuit boards to randomly stop working. I peeked through the vent slots in the back, and no circuit boards could be seen.It has 2 mechanical timers, one timer for the oven/air fry functions and one timer for the toaster function.The construction quality seems decent, stainless finish doesn't have any dents, door opens smoothly, knobs feel smooth and sturdy, seems to heat up fairly quickly. Interior light is manually operated with a button, and light it is bright. I am concerned the bulb will burn out like so many other reviews mention, but right now it seems to work fine. There is no instructions on bulb replacement in the manual.To the reviewers who say the toast function does not work, try this: the toast function on my brand new unit didn't function until I noticed that the temperature knob must be turned fully clockwise to 450 deg F for TOAST/BROIL. It has a mark on the temperature dial at 450 Deg F for "TOAST/BROIL", but it is easily overlooked.To use Toast:Set mode knob to TOAST (5 o'clock on the mode knob).Set temperature to max 450 Deg F TOAST (3 o'clock on the temperature knob).Set the right timer knob TOAST TIMER to the desired time ( light, med, dark, or 10 minutes max).Toaster works fine for me if I do the above steps.Hopefully it will keep working for years to come...time will tell.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for a smaller space
reviews.reviewText: When we moved to a new home we no longer had a convection oven and missed it for many reasons. In order to add a new appliance to our smallish space it needed to replace something we already had. So this compact machine is perfect for that, it replaced our toaster and it fits perfectly in a small corner. The air fryer function works great, we’ve tried multiple things and have been happy with all of them. I haven’t baked or roasted, but the toaster works fine. It’s also not very loud.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Toast feature does not work
reviews.reviewText: I have been using this appliance for 3 months. The air fry feature is amazing, we especially like asparagus or string beans done that way. There is plenty of room to bake chicken or a pork loin. For the first time last week, I tried to toast a bagel. The toast feature does not work! Simply doesn’t turn on. I reached out to the manufacturer and never heard back. The device is so wonderful, in every other way, but it’s ironic that something advertised, in part, as a toaster oven…doesn’t toast. Had to purchase a small toaster for our occasional bagels. Bummer.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid, Simple, and Quiet
reviews.reviewText: Simple, easy to use controls if you read the instructions. Also very QUIET. Other brands I tried were noisy, and the digital controls were awkward. The presets that different brands give you are mostly what someone else thinks works for them. I mostly ended up by passing the presets and used my own anyway. So far very happy with this purchase. One thing worth mentioning. The warrunty covers shipping back to the manufacture if needed. Also If you like the air fryer I would recommend getting the 3 year extended coverage Amazon offers. The rep told me that if anything goes out ( light, heat elements, fan) the whole unit must be replaced, not just a part. I will be very happy if we get 3 years of life.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome and quick
reviews.reviewText: This product works awesome it’s a little large for the countertop but we’ve managed to deal with it as you can make an entire meal super quick and the food is always tasted really good. The toaster works quickly. The air fryer is awesome experimented with so many different recipes. They all come out great and fast.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Completely stopped working after 5 months
reviews.reviewText: What I liked: Heated food very quickly. Got it nice a crispy. Did an awesome job cooking whatever we put in there. The price was really nice! It had a fairly small footprint for something that cooks large items. I just wish I got more than 5 months out of it!Dislikes: Stopped working after 5 months. The exterior and knobs get VERY HOT. This is what may have fried the control panel because this puts out so much heat. It's very tight trying to flip over during a cook. You have to remove the rack entirely to do this.Overall, this would have received 5 stars if it lasted longer. I can't justify anything but one star for a product that only gives you 5 months and you have to throw it away. No warranty, no returns at this point. I'd avoid it this product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I absolutely love my new oven. it was package so well. I don't believe I have ever had anything shipped to me package so well. It works so wonderfully and it actually cooks better than my actual oven. You can turn the light on and literally watch things. Fake or whatever you want to do. I love it and I'm probably gonna get one for my son and daughter-in-law.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars No customer service
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This is my first air fryer/toaster oven. Overall I do like the product but we have had a couple of problems. In less than 1 month the light bulb inside stopped working and no I didn't leave it on. In fact I think I only turned it on once or twice. The second thing that happened is the tray inside that is supposed to be dishwasher safe is falling apart. If you look in the video you can see that it is all pitted and the coating is coming off. I filed a claim with the company 17 days ago and have not received any response other than an automated one saying that they have my claim. Very disappointing customer service. One other thing to note is that if you use this like an oven then you need to add time for example if a recipe says 350° for 30 minutes it actually takes between 35 and 40 minutes in this oven.
